article.headline: Achter, Horne carry Bowling Green over Robert Morris
article.linkText: Achter, Horne carry Bowling Green over Robert Morris
article.story:
BOWLING GREEN, Ohio (AP) -- Kate Achter scored 18 points and Carin Horne added 17 to lead Bowling Green (No. 21 ESPN/USA Today; No. 25 AP) to a 92-81 win over Robert Morris on Sunday.

Bowling Green (10-2) built a commanding 73-45 lead with 9:39 left, holding the Colonials to just four offensive rebounds in the process. Robert Morris closed out the game scoring 36 points against the Falcons' back up players.

Ali Mann scored 16 points and Liz Honegger had 11 for the Falcons, who have won three straight. Bowling Green shot 48 percent from the field.

Chinata Nesbit led the Colonials (7-4) with 25 points and 10 rebounds. Psyche Butler scored 17, Sugeiry Monsac and Jenna Burkett each had 11 and Natasha Summerville added 10.
